<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n49002a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n49" href="#n49002a">N49 (VI.B.39)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n49all.htm#n49002a"> 2(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Little John he / shot</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;According to tradition, <mark>Little John</mark> (who followed his master to this country) <mark>shot</mark> an arrow from the old bridge (now Church Street bridge) to the present site of St. Michan&apos;s Church, a distance of about eleven score and seven yards, but poor Little John&apos;s great practical skill in archery could not save him from an ignominious fate; as it appears from the records of the Southwell family, he was publicly executed for robbery on Arbour Hill.&rdquo; <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO2"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 53</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
